A Florida teenager and an Atlanta woman won the overall men's and women's divisions Saturday at the annual 7 mile bridge run.

10
00:00:54,000 --> 00:01:01,000
Vaclav Berza, 15, of Big Pine Key, Florida, finished first overall.

11
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:09,000
He completed the race in 41 minutes and 1 second and claimed the top spot in the men's division.

12
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:13,000
Berza won third place in the 2022 race.

13
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:16,000
He is a student at Marathon High School.

14
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:24,000
Joanna Stevens, 28, of Atlanta, completed the course in 41 minutes and 12 seconds.

15
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:29,000
She won the women's division title and placed second overall.

16
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:34,000
The race drew competitors from 41 U.S. states.

17
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:41,000
There were also runners from other countries, including Canada, the UK and Switzerland.

18
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:48,000
The run closed the span between the middle and lower keys to traffic for three hours Saturday.

19
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:55,000
The April contest is one of the most popular running events in the southeastern United States.

20
00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:02,000
The race field filled within minutes after online registration opened in January.

