British astronaut Tim Peek is stepping down permanently from his role as a European astronaut.

27
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:04,000
He's going to take up a full-time position as ambassador for science and space instead.

28
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:07,000
Work he's been doing since 2019.

29
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:16,000
The former British Army Air Corps helicopter pilot was selected as a European Space Agency astronaut in 2009.

30
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:22,000
He flew to the space station for a six-month tour in 2015.

31
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:27,000
The tour saw him control a robot on Earth remotely from orbit.

32
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:31,000
He also helped dock to spacecraft.

33
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:36,000
Tim said, being an astronaut has been the most extraordinary experience.

34
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:44,000
I've had the privilege of working with an exceptional team of individuals during the past 13 years with the agency.

35
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:47,000
It has been incredibly exciting and rewarding.

36
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:52,000
By assuming the role of an ambassador for human flights to space,

37
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:58,000
I'll continue to support the European and the UK Space agencies.

